# Notes
#
# This is the clean, apply-ready subset from the local llama.cpp work. The broader local
# diff also contains experimental OpenVINO scheduler/device-name/debug changes used to
# analyze Qwen3.6 graph fragmentation on OpenVINO L0. That larger diff is intentionally
# not treated as an apply-ready patch because the path still produces hundreds of graph
# islands and is not performance-competitive yet.
#
# The OpenVINO exploration found these actionable issues:
# - GPU.0/GPU.1 need exact GPU-device handling instead of assuming only "GPU".
# - L0 builds do not satisfy the OpenCL remote-context path currently used by llama.cpp.
# - Qwen3.6 recurrent blocks fragment badly around SSM_CONV, GATED_DELTA_NET, L2_NORM,
#   ROPE/view inputs, and stateful KV/cache copy/update placement.
# - Basic sigmoid/softplus OpenVINO unary support reduced split count, but GATED_DELTA_NET
#   remains the dominant blocker.
